Focused on how software intended for a general audience should clearly communicate whether it is directed toward children and what data behaviors occur (or do not occur).

✅ Children’s Privacy Notice (Original / Ready to Use)

Children’s Privacy Notice

This software is intended for a general audience and is not specifically designed for children under the age of 13.

The Telepathic Wind Robot — Cyber-Mystic Analyzer does not intentionally collect, store, transmit, or process personal information from children under 13.

Current behavior of the software:

No account creation

No requests for names, email addresses, or personal identifiers

Microphone input is used only for live, local, in-browser visualization

No audio is recorded, saved, uploaded, or shared

Audio signals exist only temporarily in memory and are discarded immediately

If you are under 13:
Do not enable microphone access or use microphone-based features.

If you are a parent or guardian:
If you believe a child has used this software in a way that could involve personal information, discontinue use. The current design does not retain or store user data.

General statement:
This software is intended for experimentation and visualization only and does not function as a recording, monitoring, or data-collection tool.

⚠️ Technical Change Awareness (Children’s Privacy Trigger List)

If future versions introduce any of the following, privacy review and disclosures must be revisited:

Saving or exporting audio

Storing analysis data tied to sessions or users

User accounts, profiles, or authentication

Analytics tied to device or network identifiers

Cloud logging or remote storage

Sharing, publishing, or export features that transmit user-related data

Current safety posture:

Processing is local only

Data is not persisted

Nothing is transmitted off-device

