12/20/2025
✅ Non-Recording Visualization Disclosure (Original / Ready to Use)

Non-Recording Visualization Notice

This software uses your device’s microphone only to generate real-time visual output within your browser.

No audio is recorded

No audio is stored or saved

No audio or derived data is transmitted off-device

No sharing, uploading, or retention occurs

Audio signals are processed temporarily in memory for visualization and then discarded immediately.

This visualization does not:

create recordings or audio files

store frequency or analysis snapshots linked to a user or session

send audio to servers or third parties

associate microphone input with personal identity

Granting microphone permission enables live visual analysis only. It does not enable surveillance or monitoring.

Suggested placement locations:

Near microphone permission prompts

In a Privacy or Compliance section

In a compliance log

In a privacy.html, PRIVACY_POLICY.md, or COMPLIANCE.md file

Suggested additional sentence:

“This software is not intended to intercept, monitor, or surveil audio and does not function as a recording tool.”

Ongoing Compliance Takeaways Logged

Security expectations scale with application scope and distribution

Third-party libraries can introduce privacy or security risk

Public distribution increases scrutiny of disclosures

Devices may be lost or shared; minimize retained data

Assign clear ownership for security and compliance tasks

Collect only what is necessary and retain it briefly

Understand platform-level permissions and safeguards

Protect any authentication mechanisms if added in the future

